# Short-Read RNA-Seq Preprocessing and Alternative Splicing Pipeline

This section details the bioinformatics workflow for processing Illumina short-read RNA sequencing data. The pipeline includes adapter trimming, reference genome alignment, transcript quantification, and a comprehensive alternative splicing (AS) analysis using SUPPA2. 

System paths have been replaced with generic directory placeholders (e.g., `<RAW_DIR>`, `<TRIM_DIR>`) for clarity and reproducibility.

## 1. Quality Control and Adapter Trimming

Raw paired-end short reads are processed using `Trim Galore` to remove Nextera adapter sequences and low-quality bases.

bash
cat short_read_samples.txt | while read id; do
    trim_galore \
        --nextera \
        --paired \
        --cores 6 \
        --output_dir <TRIM_DIR> \
        <RAW_DIR>/${id}_1.fq.gz \
        <RAW_DIR>/${id}_2.fq.gz
done

cat short_read_samples.txt | while read id; do
    # 1. Align reads to the reference genome
    hisat2 -p 85 \
        -x <HISAT2_INDEX_DIR>/hs_v44 \
        --dta-cufflinks --no-mixed --no-discordant \
        -1 <TRIM_DIR>/${id}_1_val_1.fq.gz \
        -2 <TRIM_DIR>/${id}_2_val_2.fq.gz \
        -S <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.sam \
        --summary-file <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}_summary.txt
    
    # 2. Convert SAM to BAM, sort, and index
    samtools view -hb <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.sam > <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.bam
    samtools sort <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.bam -o <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.sorted.bam
    samtools index -b <ALIGN_DIR>/${id}.sorted.bam
done



# 1. Quantify transcript abundance for each sample
cat short_read_samples.txt | while read id; do
    salmon quant \
        -p 80 -l A \
        -i <SALMON_INDEX_DIR>/transcripts_index \
        -1 <TRIM_DIR>/${id}_val_1.fq \
        -2 <TRIM_DIR>/${id}_val_2.fq \
        -o <SALMON_OUT_DIR>/${id}_quant
done

# 2. Merge TPM (Transcripts Per Million) values
salmon quantmerge \
    --quants <SALMON_OUT_DIR>/P*_quant \
    --column TPM \
    -o <SALMON_OUT_DIR>/transcript_SR.TPM.csv

# 3. Merge raw NumReads (for differential gene expression)
salmon quantmerge \
    --quants <SALMON_OUT_DIR>/P*_quant \
    --column NumReads \
    -o <SALMON_OUT_DIR>/transcript_SR.num.csv



